headline: Alexandria Real Estate Equities: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The real estate investment trust, based in Pasadena, California, said it had funds from operations of $396.4 million, or $2.33 per share, in the period. The average estimate of four analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of $2.29 per share. Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry.
